{
  "texts": [
    "The BBN dataset created in the same period not only introduced more new entity categories but also provided a more detailed delineation of entity categories.",
    "Specifically, BBN proposes 12 named entity types, 9 nominal entity types, and 7 numeric types [35].",
    "OntoNotes 5.0, proposed in 2013, contains 18 named entity categories, which are broadly consistent with the BBN entity categories as it draws somewhat on the BBN dataset's entity category delineation.When researchers are annotating NER datasets created based on the biomedical domain, the entities of interest are very different from when annotating newswire texts.",
    "For example, the GENIA project, set up to promote the development and evaluation of information extraction in the medical field, focused on gene and protein and cell identification [25,26], followed by the GENETAG dataset and the PROGENE dataset, which focused only on gene and protein recognition.",
    "Since then, research in the biomedical field has been in full swing, and specific research in this area has become more practically oriented."
  ]
}